reviewText: Callan Pinkney's workout's may be dated but if you can look past the leotards you won't be disappointed. If you are consistent and do this workout as she instructs it will deliver results. It lifts and tightens the entire body, plus it's gentle on the joints. It's very slow moving and relaxing so it's nice at the end of the day when you want to wind down. If you are the type that like fast movement and upbeat tunes while your working out then this isn't for you.

reviewText: I have been doing Callanetics for the last 9 months.I have lost 25 inches and 15 lbs.Exercises had become easy for me and have not had any more results recently.I decided to buy Super Callaneticss.  All I can say is WOW.These exercises are tough and NOT for a beginner.I was physically exhausted after 30 minutes.I did not become sore but definitely felt the firming and tightness working around by midsection.It was almost like wearing a corset.It states that doing 1 set of these exercises equals 20 sessions from "10/10" and I believe it.I bought the "10/10" classic DVD to give to my MIL as a present.
summary: Wow - they don't call it Super for nothing

reviewText: This is my favorite exercise video.  Very slow and relaxing but extremely challenging.  Very low impact.  The nice thing about this is that you can just do less repetitions and still finish the video and do all of the various exercises.

reviewText: I used to do these stretches and don't know why I stopped. I had a VHS tape. Callan really worked muscles and toned the body with such low/no impact it was amazing. I laughed when my teens, who were chuckling at me, couldn't keep up! They developed a lot of respect for these routines and started working our with me. I was delighted to rediscover these great exercises in DVD format.

reviewText: This is a great exercise program.  I owned the VHS tape over 20 years ago and had forgotten how much I enjoyed doing the exercises (also had forgotten what leotards looked like).  She is a splendid instructor but the movements certainly seem more difficult now than when I did them 20 years ago; I will keep working on it and know that it will become easier eventually.  This is a nice change of pace from Pilates and yoga.
